name: Ken Page
summary: Ken Page, a prominent Broadway star and voice actor, passed away at the age of 70. Page is best known for his portrayal of Old Deuteronomy in the Broadway production of "Cats," as well as his voice role as Oogie Boogie in Tim Burton's "The Nightmare Before Christmas." He also appeared in the Muny stage productions and other Broadway shows. Page's passing has been widely reported in news outlets such as The New York Times, ABC News, USA Today, Los Angeles Times, and others, highlighting his contributions to the entertainment industry both on stage and in film.

name: Alma Police Department Morgan Nick
summary: Authorities in Arkansas have announced significant developments in the decades-old kidnapping case of Morgan Nick. DNA evidence has linked Billy Jack Lincks, a suspect in her 1995 disappearance, to a truck that once belonged to him. This discovery follows years of investigation and the recent connection made between Nick's DNA and the suspect through genetic genealogy. The Alma Police Department, along with other agencies, will provide further details and updates on the case. The news has brought renewed hope to those who have long awaited answers in Morgan Nick's disappearance and potential resolution to this tragic event.

name: Breast Cancer Awareness Month
summary: October has been designated as Breast Cancer Awareness Month, serving as an important reminder for preventive care. The Texas Health and Human Services encourages individuals to prioritize screenings during this period. Various organizations, including CBS News, the Association of Flight Attendants-CWA, and Hard Rock International, are actively promoting awareness and supporting research initiatives. Statistics indicate the prevalence of breast cancer and highlight the significance of early detection. Local efforts, such as those in New Orleans and the Michigan Peninsula, are raising funds and raising awareness through events like bike rides and painting campaigns. Additionally, the NBA is partnering with TODAY to distribute items that support the cause. The International Agency for Research on Cancer (IARC) is also recognizing this month with a focus on global awareness.
